quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  13,32,"Other messengers had already been ridiculed before you, but I delayed the disbelievers ňĻfor a whileňļ then seized them. And how ňĻhorribleňļ was My punishment"
  13,33,"Is ňĻthere any equal toňļ the Vigilant One Who knows what every soul commits? Yet the pagans have associated others with Allah ňĻin worshipňļ. Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúName them! Or do you ňĻmean toňļ inform Him of something He does not know on the earth? Or are these ňĻgodsňļ just empty words?‚ÄĚ In fact, the disbelievers‚Äô falsehood has been made so appealing to them that they have been turned away from the Path. And whoever Allah leaves to stray will be left with no guide"
  13,34,"For them is punishment in this worldly life, but the punishment of the Hereafter is truly far worse. And none can shield them from Allah"
  13,35,The description of the Paradise promised to the righteous is that under it rivers flow; eternal is its fruit as well as its shade. That is the ňĻultimateňļ outcome for the righteous. But the outcome for the disbelievers is the Fire
  13,36,"ňĻThe believers amongňļ those who were given the Scripture rejoice at what has been revealed to you ňĻO Prophetňļ, while some ňĻdisbelievingňļ factions deny a portion of it. Say, ‚ÄúI have only been commanded to worship Allah, associating none with Him ňĻin worshipňļ. To Him I invite ňĻallňļ, and to Him is my return.‚ÄĚ"
  13,37,"And so We have revealed it as an authority in Arabic. And if you were to follow their desires after ňĻallňļ the knowledge that has come to you, there would be none to protect or shield you from Allah"